VSCode Version: 1.8.1
OS Version: OS X 10.11.6

The following valid less is incorrectly marked with red squiggles:

    .media-switch(@styles) {
        @media(orientation:landscape){
            @styles();
        }
    }

A similar issue happens when passing a detached ruleset to the mixin:

    .media-switch({
        flex-direction: row;
    });

See also [issue 131](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/131).

![screen shot 2017-01-12 at 14 37 45](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3245228/21891816/bfd0134e-d8d4-11e6-84f3-2eccb2752d50.png)

<img width="202" alt="screen shot 2017-01-13 at 13 00 35" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3245228/21929349/5628c244-d990-11e6-9c06-f8c56c79af0d.png">

- VSCode Version: 1.8.1
- OS Version: Linux

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Write following code
```
#include <iostream>

namespace someName{
    void someMethod1(){
        int n = 6;
        return n;
    }

    void someMethod2(){
        int n = 6;
        return n;
    }
}

int main(){}
```

2. Try to fold code b/w namespace, no [+] icon is shown in gutter.
